### âœ… Test Locally

Once your app is running on `localhost:8080`, access:

* ðŸ”¹ `/reconcile/exclude` â€“ performs exclusion and shows excluded count.
* ðŸ”¹ `/reconcile/nonexcluded` â€“ shows current non-excluded ALGO and STAR counts.
* ðŸ”¹ `/reconcile/match/{type}` â€“ performs matching on non-excluded data. `{type}` can be `one-to-one`, `one-to-many`, `many-to-one`, `many-to-many`.

Let me know if you'd like to return the full records in `/nonexcluded`, or persist any of these results in a DB.
